(1.1 MIT Athena and DSSA) show newline
(-----------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Cyberspace traces its lineage to MIT's Athena project and the) show newline
(Distributed System Security Architecture \(DSSA\) research that produced) show newline
(SPKI.) show newline
() show newline
(Athena introduced Kerberos, distributed authentication, and the concept) show newline
(of a unified computing environment across heterogeneous systems. DSSA,) show newline
(led by Rivest, Lampson, and Ellison, gave us SPKI - capability-based) show newline
(authorization through certificate chains.) show newline
() show newline
(These ideas were absorbed during the same lamport epoch as R4RS Scheme) show newline
(\(1991\) and SDSI \(1996\), alongside the practical education of Boston) show newline
(traffic negotiation - both exercises in asserting authority without) show newline
(central coordination.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(1.2 Why Scheme) show newline
(--------------) show newline
() show newline
(Scheme was chosen not for nostalgia but for precision. Homoiconicity) show newline
(makes S-expressions natural for both code and data - certificates, audit) show newline
(records, and configuration are all readable by the same parser that) show newline
(reads the implementation.) show newline
() show newline
(The language that Abelson and Sussman used to teach computational) show newline
(thinking at MIT is the same language used to implement the security) show newline
(architecture that MIT research defined. Full circle.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(2. COLLABORATIVE DESIGN) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Cyberspace was designed in collaboration with Claude \(Anthropic\), an AI) show newline
(assistant. This collaboration is documented in Memo-056.) show newline
() show newline
(The interaction model: human provides vision and constraints, AI) show newline
(provides implementation and exploration. Neither could have built this) show newline
(alone.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
